---
import PageLayout from '@/layouts/PageLayout.astro';
---

<PageLayout
  title="Changelog"
  description="Release history for VMFlux products."
>
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6 py-16 lg:px-8">
    <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-brand-600">Changelog</p>
    <h1 class="mt-3 text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-foreground">Product updates</h1>
    <p class="mt-6 max-w-3xl text-lg text-foreground-muted">
      Public release history for VMFlux products and the current roadmap.
    </p>

    <div class="mt-12 space-y-8">
      <div class="rounded-3xl border border-border bg-card p-8">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-brand-600">
          Current release
        </p>
        <h2 class="mt-3 text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-foreground">
          VMFlux OBJ Exporter v3.2.6
        </h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-base leading-7 text-foreground-muted">
          Current public release of the VMFlux OBJ Exporter for Navisworks.
        </p>

        <div class="mt-8 grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2">
          <div class="rounded-2xl border border-border bg-background p-5">
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-foreground">Supported versions</p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-foreground-muted">
              Navisworks 2024 / 2025 / 2026
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="rounded-2xl border border-border bg-background p-5">
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-foreground">Current export format</p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-foreground-muted">
              OBJ + MTL
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <ul class="mt-8 space-y-3 text-sm leading-7 text-foreground-muted">
          <li>Support for Navisworks 2024 / 2025 / 2026</li>
          <li>OBJ + MTL export workflow</li>
          <li>Per-instance group export structure</li>
          <li>Material naming and transparency support</li>
          <li>Selected Models / Entire Model export scope</li>
          <li>Units dropdown with “Keep numeric values (no unit scaling)” option</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="rounded-3xl border border-border bg-card p-8">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-brand-600">
          Release notes
        </p>
        <h2 class="mt-3 text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-foreground">
          v3.2.6 highlights
        </h2>

        <div class="mt-6 grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2">
          <div class="rounded-2xl border border-border bg-background p-5">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-foreground">Exporter maturity</h3>
            <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-6 text-foreground-muted">
              Stable current release aligned to supported Navisworks versions and practical export workflows.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="rounded-2xl border border-border bg-background p-5">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-foreground">Material-aware output</h3>
            <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-6 text-foreground-muted">
              Includes real Navisworks material naming and transparency handling in MTL output.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="rounded-2xl border border-border bg-background p-5">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-foreground">Scope control</h3>
            <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-6 text-foreground-muted">
              Supports Selected Models and Entire Model export scope for targeted or full-model workflows.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="rounded-2xl border border-border bg-background p-5">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-foreground">Units control</h3>
            <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-6 text-foreground-muted">
              Includes practical output units selection and optional no-scaling numeric export behavior.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="rounded-3xl border border-border bg-muted/50 p-8">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-brand-600">
          Planned next
        </p>
        <h2 class="mt-3 text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-foreground">
          Roadmap
        </h2>
        <ul class="mt-6 space-y-3 text-sm leading-7 text-foreground-muted">
          <li>GLB / glTF export</li>
          <li>Properties export</li>
          <li>Expanded downstream workflow coverage</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</PageLayout>